desc: 1:30hour via train from London Victoria is Arundel Castle, recently re-opened for visitors and one of the most beautiful places I've ever visited in England.   Founded in 1067 by the Earl of Arundel, this medieval castle has been the home of the Dukes of Norfolk for the past 800 years, and as you learn, it becomes impossible to imagine English history without the part played by this powerful family. üìö To name a few, the 3rd Duke of Norfolk was uncle of Anne Boleyn and Catherine Howard.
